"This health course will focus on the mental health issues of people with intellectual disability.
You will learn about the complexities of diagnosing mental health issues in people with intellectual disabilities and the types of disorders, assessments, screenings, and treatments used. There will also be a special focus on the legal and ethical complexities in health practice with patients who often require substituted consent."	"mental health issues and disorders
mental health assessments and screenings
challenging behaviors
treatments
legal and ethical issues"
